# Scorpio Carwash Web — Core Rules

Read and follow all instructions in `.ai/instructions.md`. That file is the single source of truth for architecture, conventions, and coding patterns.

## Quick Reference

- JavaScript (`.js`, `.jsx`) only — no TypeScript
- React Router v7 framework mode, SSR via `react-router.config.js`
- Single admin segment at `/admin` (maps to Jod Team portal pattern)
- react-bootstrap + Bootstrap 5 SCSS for UI
- react-hook-form + zod for forms
- `adminApiClient` in `app/api/ky-client.js` for all API calls
- URL-driven list/filter state (`useSearchParams`)
- All admin pages: `robots: noindex, nofollow`

## Anti-Patterns (NEVER Do These)

1. NEVER call APIs from passive view components
2. NEVER use TypeScript
3. NEVER use Tailwind — use Bootstrap SCSS
4. NEVER put domain forms in `app/components/`
5. NEVER import `AdminPageShell` in page components
6. NEVER skip `meta` export on route pages
7. NEVER use `process.env.VITE_*` — use `import.meta.env`
